{"title_page": "On Green Dolphin Street (song)", "text_new": "{{other uses|Green Dolphin Street (disambiguation)}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = On Green Dolphin Street\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = song\n| artist     = [[Jimmy Dorsey]]\n| album      =\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = 1947\n| released   =\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = Pop, jazz\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| writer     =\n| composer   = [[Bronis\u0142aw Kaper]]\n| lyricist   = [[Ned Washington]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| title      =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n'''\"On Green Dolphin Street\"''' (originally titled \"Green Dolphin Street\") is a 1947 popular song composed by [[Bronis\u0142aw Kaper]] with lyrics by [[Ned Washington]]. The song was composed for the film ''[[Green Dolphin Street (film)|Green Dolphin Street]],'' which was based on a 1944 novel of the same name by [[Elizabeth Goudge]], and became a jazz standard after it was recorded by [[Miles Davis]] in 1958.<ref>[http://www.jazzstandards.com/compositions-0/ongreendolphinstreet.htm \"On Green Dolphin Street\" at jazzstandards.com]</ref>\n\n== Renditions ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Main recording artist\n! scope=\"col\" | Vocalist\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Album title, notes\n|-\n| 1947 || [[Jimmy Dorsey|Jimmy Dorsey Orchestra]] || Bill Lawrence || Soundtrack for ''[[Green Dolphin Street (film)|Green Dolphin Street]]''\n|-\n| 1955 || [[Urbie Green]] || instrumental || ''East Coast Jazz Volume 6'' (1955) ]\n|-\n| 1956 || [[Ahmad Jamal]] Trio || instrumental || ''[[Count 'Em 88]]''<ref name=\"standards\">{{cite book |last1=Gioia |first1=Ted |title=The Jazz Standards: A Guide to the Repertoire |date=2012 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York City |isbn=978-0-19-993739-4 |page=314}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1957 |