ilson]] || instrumental || soundtrack ''[[The Score (2001 film)|The Score]]''\n|-\n| 2001 || [[Keith Jarrett]] / [[Gary Peacock]] / [[Jack DeJohnette]] || instrumental || ''[[My Foolish Heart (Keith Jarrett album)|My Foolish Heart \u2013 Live at Montreux]]'' (2007)\n|-\n| 2002 || [[George Coleman]], [[Mike Stern]], [[Ron Carter]] & [[Jimmy Cobb]] || instrumental || ''Four Generations of Miles''\n|-\n| 2006 || [[Austin Peralta]] || instrumental || ''Maiden Voyage''\n|-\n| 2009 || [[Chick Corea]], [[Stanley Clarke]], [[Lenny White]] || instrumental || ''Forever'' (2011)\n|-\n| 2012 || [[Cory Henry]] || instrumental || ''Gotcha Now Doc''\n|-\n| 2014 || [[Gordon Goodwin]]'s Big Phat Band || instrumental || ''Life in the Bubble''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1940s jazz standards]]\n[[Category:1947 songs]]\n[[Category:Songs with lyrics by Ned Washington]]\n[[Category:Songs with music by Bronis\u0142aw Kaper]]\n", "text_old": "{{other uses|Green Dolphin Street (disambiguation)}}\n{{refimprove|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = On Green Dolphin Street\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| type       = song\n| artist     = [[Jimmy Dorsey]]\n| album      =\n| EP         =\n| written    =\n| published  = 1947\n| released   =\n| format     =\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = Pop, jazz\n| length     =\n| label      =\n| writer     =\n| composer   = [[Bronis\u0142aw Kaper]]\n| lyricist   = [[Ned Washington]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| title      =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}}\n\n'''\"On Green Dolphin Street\"''' (originally titled \"Green Dolphin Street\") is a 1947 popular song composed by [[Bronis\u0142aw Kaper]] with lyrics by [[Ned Washington]]. The song was composed for the film ''[[Green Dolphin Street (film)|Green Dolphin Street]],'' which was based on a 1944 novel of the same name by [[Elizabeth Goudge]], and became a jazz standard after it was recorded by [[Miles Davis]] in 1958.<ref>[http://www.jazzstandards.com/compositions-0/ongreendolphinstreet.htm \"On Green Dolphin Street\" at jazzstandards.com]</ref>\n\n== Renditions ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Main recording artist\n! scope=\"col\" | Vocalist\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Album title, notes\n|-\n| 1947 || [[Jimmy Dorsey|Jimmy Dorsey Orchestra]] || Bill Lawrence || Soundtrack for ''[[Green Dolphin Street (film)|Green Dolphin Street]]''\n|-\n| 1955 || [[Urbie Green]] || instrumental || ''East Coast Jazz Volume 6'' (1955) ]\n|-\n| 1956 || [[Ahmad Jamal]] Trio || instrumental || ''[[Count 'Em 88]]''<ref name=\"standards\">{{cite book |last1=Gioia |first1=Ted |title=The Jazz Standards: A Guide to the Repertoire |date=2012 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York City |isbn=978-0-19-993739-4 |page=314}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1957 || Poll Winners ([[Barney Kessel]], [[Ray Brown (musician)|Ray Brown]], [[Shelly Manne]]) || instrumental || ''The Poll Winners''\n|-\n|1957 || [[Chet Baker]] || instrumental || ''[[Embraceable You (album)|Embraceable You]]''\n|-\n| 1958 || [[Jack Sheldon]] and His Exciting All-Star Big-Band || instrumental || ''Jack's Groove'', arranged for big band by [[Lenny Niehaus]]\n|-\n| 1958 || [[Miles Davis]] Sextet || instrumental || ''[[Jazz Track]]'' (with soundtrack ''[[Ascenseur pour l'\u00e9chafaud (soundtrack)|Ascenseur pour l'\u00e9chafaud]]''), reissued as ''[[Basic Miles: The Classic Performances of Miles Davis|Basic Miles]]'' (1973) and ''[[1958 Miles]]''<ref name=\"standards\" /> in Japan (1974), (also '' '58 Miles Featuring Stella by Starlight'')\n|-\n| 1958 || [[Anthony Perkins|Tony Perkins]] with [[Urbie Green]]'s Orchestra || [[Anthony Perkins|Tony Perkins]] || ''From My Heart...'' \n|-\n| 1959 || [[Bill Evans]] || instrumental || ''[[On Green Dolphin Street (Bill Evans album)|On Green Dolphin Street]]''<ref name=\"standards\" />\n|-\n| 1959 || [[Wynton Kelly]] || instrumental || ''[[