die \"Lockjaw\" Davis]] || instrumental || ''Leapin' on Lenox''<ref name=\"standards\" />\n|-\n| 1974 || [[Herb Ellis]] & [[Ray Brown (musician)|Ray Brown]] || instrumental || ''Herb Ellis & Ray Brown's Soft Shoe''\n|-\n| 1974 || [[Lee Konitz]] || instrumental || ''[[Satori (Lee Konitz album)|Satori]]''\n|-\n| 1974 || [[Oscar Peterson]] Trio || instrumental || ''[[Oscar Peterson in Russia]]''\n|-\n| 1975 || [[The Singers Unlimited|Singers Unlimited]] with [[Patrick Williams (composer)|Pat Williams]] Orchestra || [[The Singers Unlimited]] || ''Feeling Free''\n|-\n| 1976 || [[Joe Pass]] (solo)|| instrumental || ''[[Virtuoso No. 2]]''\n|-\n| 1976 || [[Joe Sample]] / [[Ray Brown (musician)|Ray Brown]] / [[Shelly Manne]] || instrumental || ''The Three''\n|-\n| 1976 || [[Monty Alexander]] || instrumental || ''Unlimited Love - Live & In Concert''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Archie Shepp]] || instrumental || ''On Green Dolphin Street''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Benny Carter]] 4 || instrumental || ''Montreux '77'', live \n|-\n| 1977 || [[Carmen McRae]] || [[Carmen McRae]] || ''At the Great American Music Hall'', recorded live with a quartet featuring [[Dizzy Gillespie]]\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Les Brown (bandleader)|Les Brown]] & His Band of Renown || instrumental || ''Goes Direct to Disc''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Masabumi Kikuchi]] Sextet || instrumental || ''Matrix''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Return to Forever]] || instrumental || ''[[Live (Return to Forever album)|Live: The Complete Concert]]''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Rhoda Scott]] and [[Kenny Clarke]] || [[Rhoda Scott]] || ''Rhoda Scott + Kenny Clarke'', reissued as ''Jazz in Paris''\n|-\n| 1977 || [[Sheila Jordan]] & [[Arild Andersen]] || [[Sheila Jordan]] || ''Sheila''\n|-\n| 1978 || [[Herbie Hancock]] || instrumental || ''[[The Piano (Herbie Hancock album)|The Piano]]''\n|-\n| 1978 || [[Woody Shaw]] Quintet || instrumental || ''[[Stepping Stones Bonus Tracks (Woody Shaw album)|Stepping Stones Bonus Tracks]]'' (2011), recorded live at the Village Vanguard\n|-\n| 1979 